author: Julia McCoy
description:
*Note:* Examples discussed are illustrative only and not guarantees of income.

The AI space moves fast, and while these models are based on current market trends and documented case studies, they require professional-level execution. This is not a 'passive income' guide.

*Hundreds of billions of dollars are flowing into AI in 2025*—yet most companies still struggle to use it effectively. That gap may represent an opportunity for builders willing to develop real skills and execute consistently. In this video, I break down 5 AI business models early adopters are using, from solo-built tools to scalable service businesses.

*The 5 models:*
*AI SaaS Apps* – Niche tools built by small teams or solo founders, based on publicly reported case studies.
*AI Marketing Services* – Chatbots, automations, and workflow systems used by high-leverage agencies.
*AI Content Strategy* – Applying AI to YouTube growth, consulting, and premium content workflows.

title: Best AI Businesses to Start on Your Own (Real Numbers Revealed)
